## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Excellent pair (e.g., Viscaria, Timo Boll ALC). Rozena tames the stiffness of outer carbon, creating a highly balanced, forgiving setup for intermediate attackers.
    - Inner Carbon: Great for players seeking maximum dwell time and a high safety margin (e.g., Innerforce ALC).
    - All-Wood: Perfect for beginners or all-round players (e.g., Korbel). It maximizes feeling and control.
    - Mismatch Cases: Very soft, slow all-wood blades might make Rozena feel too mushy and lacking in finishing power.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Great for developing players learning their strokes, but advanced players will outgrow its top-end speed and spin quickly.
    - Backhand: Exceptional. Its blocking stability, forgiveness on receive, and easy lifting make it a top-tier backhand rubber for a wide range of skill levels.

